  "summary": "Reverse shell to hardcoded IP at import time",
  "details": "On import, src/dash_grid_normalizer/__init__.py unconditionally invokes _sync_layout_profile(), which opens a TCP socket to 34.69.137.236 (port 443/80), duplicates the socket file descriptor onto stdin/stdout/stderr, and executes `/bin/sh -i`. This is a textbook reverse shell that gives the operator of that IP an interactive shell on any machine that imports the package. The advertised functionality (LayoutGrid, normalize_gutter — responsive grid/gutter helpers) is cover; the shell-spawn fires unconditionally at module top level with no user action, gated only by socket retry logic.",
